R100

Load Bank Pre-Start Checklist

Comprehensive Equipment Inspection Form

⚠️ Safety Notice

This task should be performed by appropriately qualified personnel only prior to applying any load to satisfy safety concerns.

A

Visual Inspection#1

1
Verify all heater coils are in horizontal zig-zag pattern.
2
Verify all external fastners are secured. If required, remove exhaust grill to check the hardware.
3
If any fastner is loose or missing, load bank may have more/other fastners loose. Tighten all fastner prior to moving next step.
B

Visual Inspection#2

4
Verify all internal & external surfaces are free of any water or liquid drops.
5
Verify MICA strips are not unlaminated. Such delamination occurs when direct water spray has occurred causing delamination.
C

Resistane check to prevent short circuit.

6
Ensure no connections are made to the Load Bank Camlok connectors.
7
Ensure voltage selection switch is OFF (center position) and not on 480VAC/240VAC position.
8
Ensure first load step switch from LHS is OFF (center position).
9
Ensure other four load step switches are OFF (down position).
10
Ensure load switch is OFF (down position).
11
Verify resistance between following jacks:
12
A-B: Open (Infinity)
13
